    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-29T07:29:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-29T07:29:00-05:00" n="588"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d588">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1987</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Moscow</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PDC1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Poole</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]<note n="1" xml:id="d588fn1">Printed
                            in full in <ref target="frus1918Russiav01#pg_545">vol. <hi
                                    rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 545</ref>.</note>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-29T15:00:00+02:31">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 29, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received June 9, 10.21 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>576. … <persName>Halsey</persName> telegraphs from Murman May 25: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Notwithstanding orders received direct from Moscow Commissariat Foreign
                            Affairs, district Soviet desires Allies to remain. They <pb facs="0567"
                                n="477" xml:id="pg_477"/> inform me in writing that their feelings
                            toward United States are most sincere and cordial and that this
                            friendship will only be cemented by presence American warship. <hi
                                rend="italic">Olympia</hi> arrived 24th and is under orders British
                            admiral.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Bolsheviks probably hope that by Murman cession to Finland they can avoid issue
                    through direct clash between Allies on one side and Finland and Germany on
                    other. …</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PDC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Poole</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
